Let $
abla$ be an affine connection on a smooth manifold $\mathcal M$ . We say $
abla$ is torsion-free if for any vector fields $X, Y$ on $\mathcal M$ , we have  egin{equation} 
abla_X Y - 
abla_Y X = [X, Y], \end{equation} where $[X, Y] = X \circ Y - Y \circ X$ is the Lie bracket of $X$ and $Y$ . Is it equivalent to state the torsion-free property as  egin{equation} 
abla_X Y = X \circ Y \end{equation} for all vector fields $X, Y$ ? Why or why not?
